# Wateray Baseline

- Keep module boundaries: UI in `app/`, engine in `core/`, automation in `scripts/`.
- Keep TUN adapter persistent during node switches. Update outbound through hot reload APIs.
- Run core engine asynchronously and expose non-blocking FFI APIs to UI.
- Load user-facing strings from external JSON under `app/assets/i18n/`.
- Changes touching tunnel or routing must include verification steps.

## Example

```text
BAD: stop core -> destroy tun -> recreate tun on each node switch
GOOD: keep tun alive -> hot reload outbound -> continue traffic accounting
```
